Seq1.ReceiverContent: Good morning. Thank you for calling Crofton Family Practice. This is Kathy. How may I assist you today?

Seq2.CallerContent: Is it Brandy? You are Brandy?
Seq2.ReceiverContent: So would you like to speak to Brandy? Yes. Good morning. I'm going to stay online. I'm transferring the call and have a great day.

Seq4.ReceiverContent: Thank you for contacting Crofton Family Practice. This is Brandy here in the front office. How can we help you today?

Seq5.CallerContent: Brandy, how are you? Good morning first.

Seq6.CallerContent: Do you remember I called you about my labs for a month ago?

Seq8.CallerContent: No, no, no. You sent me, but I didn't see the liquid profile. Can you please transfer to the lab lady?
Seq8.ReceiverContent: Yeah, I can definitely go ahead and transfer you in there. Remember, that's what I was going to say. We spoke about whether or not I wasn't sure if they were going to draw that or not. So, yes, indeed, sir. Let me go ahead and send you in to our lab coordinator, Lori, okay?

Seq9.ReceiverContent: Yes, sir. No problem, Mr. M. Blum. Here we go.

Seq10.CallerContent: Sorry, I can't come to the phone right now. I'm either with a patient or away from my desk. Leave your name and number and a brief message, and I will get back to you as soon as possible. Thank you.

Seq11.CallerContent: Bori, this is Dr. M. Blum. You took my lab on 14th of September. I wonder, I did not get the liquid profile results. Could you please check whether you have sent the liquid profile? Thank you. And please call me, 301-455-9004. Thank you.
